result.reason: TigerVNC (Java/AWT) embedded via SetParent loses keyboard input due to fundamental Win32/Java interop limitation; mRemoteNG has built-in VNC protocol support that handles keyboard input correctly
result.approach: Users should use mRemoteNG built-in VNC protocol instead of embedding TigerVNC Java; fixing keyboard forwarding for Java AWT windows embedded via SetParent is outside project scope
